1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:07,200
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:08,167 --> 00:00:10,167
If it is proven that you are not
a real Torrecampo,

3
00:00:10,300 --> 00:00:12,767
you will lose all your wealth,

4
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:15,600
the name you use,
to get everything you want.

5
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:17,700
He just wants me
to feel small,

6
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,400
but I will not fall
into his trap.

7
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:20,633
I'll stop him

8
00:00:20,767 --> 00:00:22,333
before he spreads the things
he's been saying about me.

9
00:00:22,467 --> 00:00:24,467
Mom, if what Aldrin
is saying is true,

10
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,000
Paolo deserves to know.

11
00:00:26,133 --> 00:00:29,867
The accusation by Mr. Greg
Torrecampo is serious.

12
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,633
How can you be sure that he had
nothing to do with the fire?

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,700
Because I know
who the real culprit is.

14
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,200
Who, Miss?

15
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:46,833
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:55,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

17
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:08,933
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

18
00:01:11,267 --> 00:01:16,400
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

19
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,300
What kind of nonsense is this?

20
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:28,700
What are you talking about?

21
00:01:29,933 --> 00:01:32,667
Don't be mad at me, Paolo.

22
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:35,933
In fact, you should be thanking
me for telling you the truth.

23
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:38,800
You're just making this up.

24
00:01:39,567 --> 00:01:41,433
Everyone knows
how desperate you are

25
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:43,100
to destroy my family.

26
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:47,067
So now, you're even dragging
my identity into this?

27
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:50,533
You just made this up
to stir trouble in my family.

28
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:54,700
Paolo, you don't want to believe
it because you're afraid.

29
00:01:56,633 --> 00:01:59,033
You're afraid
that if it's proven

30
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:00,500
that you're not
a real Torrecampo...

31
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,633
you'll lose everything.

32
00:02:05,100 --> 00:02:07,633
The wealth, the position...

33
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,300
the name you use
to get everything.

34
00:02:12,433 --> 00:02:13,467
Isn't that right?

35
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:18,567
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:19,933
Stop it!

37
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:23,333
I'll smash your face.

38
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:26,367
- [CHUCKLES]
- Go ahead, Paolo.

39
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:27,733
Punch me.

40
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,433
Hit me with everything
that you got!

41
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:33,433
But it won't change the fact

42
00:02:33,567 --> 00:02:37,333
that your entire life
is a massive lie.

43
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:38,567
And don't be angry at me

44
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,833
because I'm not the one
who deceived you.

45
00:02:41,867 --> 00:02:44,367
Be angry at your own mother.

46
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:47,067
Because she became an expert
at hiding your family's dirt.

47
00:02:48,667 --> 00:02:51,467
She lied to you
from the day you were born.

48
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:59,133
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:03,133
You won't destroy my family
with your lies.

50
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:11,600
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:21,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:03:21,267 --> 00:03:24,733
What's Aldrin's basis
for saying all those things?

53
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:27,467
Marj, that's Aldrin.

54
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,667
We know how dirty he plays.

55
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,300
And he'll do anything
to see our family fall apart.

56
00:03:33,033 --> 00:03:34,133
I know, Pao.

57
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:38,767
But for me,
for your peace of mind,

58
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,933
why don't you ask
and talk to your mother

59
00:03:41,067 --> 00:03:42,567
to know the truth?

60
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,733
No, I won't do that.

61
00:03:44,867 --> 00:03:47,767
I will not insult my mother
by questioning her integrity.

62
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:50,633
Just because of that conspiracy
theory of Aldrin?

63
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,833
Where is Paolo?
He's over there, Ma'am.

64
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,333
He just wants me to question
my own identity.

65
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,267
He just wants me to feel small.

66
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,800
So that no one stands in his way
of taking over the company.

67
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:10,800
But I will not fall
into his trap.

68
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:12,433
- But, Pao...
- He just wants

69
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:14,267
Edward and me to fight.

70
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,000
But I won't let that happen.

71
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:17,233
Because I'll stop him

72
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:20,000
before he spreads what
he's been saying about me.

73
00:04:20,133 --> 00:04:22,467
<i> Why would they fight?</i>

74
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:25,533
<i>And why is Paolo so triggered
by what Aldrin said?</i>

75
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:30,467
Good evening.

76
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:32,400
Thea.

77
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,733
Have you been there long?

78
00:04:36,167 --> 00:04:36,900
No.

79
00:04:37,033 --> 00:04:38,300
I just arrived.

80
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:42,167
I just wanted to check if you
spoke again with Ms. Yolly.

81
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:48,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

82
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:51,667
Mom, sorry for the inconvenience

83
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:56,200
but I can't ignore
what Aldrin said.

84
00:04:57,633 --> 00:04:59,767
That Paolo is supposedly
your illegitimate child.

85
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:03,500
I knew it.

86
00:05:03,633 --> 00:05:05,200
Aldrin is truly desperate now.

87
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:09,533
He's saying all kinds of things
that aren't even true.

88
00:05:09,667 --> 00:05:10,633
Right?

89
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:16,800
Why do you even pay attention
to that person's attacks?

90
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:19,200
It's just a waste of your time,
Marj.

91
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,100
Mom, I want to hear it
from you.

92
00:05:22,233 --> 00:05:24,067
So that next time we see him,

93
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,500
we have a defense.

94
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:28,933
And so we can prove
that he's lying.

95
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,467
[CHUCKLES]

96
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,500
You know what, Marj?

97
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,667
I forgot I have an appointment.

98
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,867
There are much more
important things

99
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,433
I need to attend to
than that worthless issue.

100
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:44,100
But why can't you say
that it's not true?

101
00:05:44,867 --> 00:05:46,267
Mom, just yes or no.

102
00:05:48,533 --> 00:05:50,433
Unless you're hiding something.

103
00:05:52,967 --> 00:05:54,667
Mom, if Aldrin is telling
the truth,

104
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,567
Paolo deserves to know.

105
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:58,967
Because he could use this
against him.

106
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:02,433
This might be the only way
for Edward to be freed.

107
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:05,300
If dad finds out that
Edward is his real child,

108
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:07,900
he might not continue
the lawsuit.

109
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:10,033
Mom, what is the truth?

110
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:15,967
Marj, you don't understand.

111
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,767
If Greg finds out...

112
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:22,800
he'll disown Paolo.

113
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:25,700
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

114
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,467
So, it's true, Mom?

115
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:31,600
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,867
Ms. Yolly?

117
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,067
What are you doing here?

118
00:06:37,733 --> 00:06:40,567
Ms. Yolly Natividad
is here to give a statement.

119
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,600
She claims she knows something
about your case.

120
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,533
Really? Ms. Yolly...

121
00:06:46,667 --> 00:06:47,967
Ms. Yolly, thank you.

122
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,500
I knew it,
you wouldn't abandon me.

123
00:06:50,633 --> 00:06:55,033
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:06:58,533 --> 00:06:59,567
Yes.

125
00:07:00,367 --> 00:07:01,333
[SIGHS]

126
00:07:02,433 --> 00:07:03,467
Paolo.

127
00:07:06,433 --> 00:07:08,933
Paolo was the result
of my affair back then.

128
00:07:09,067 --> 00:07:14,200
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

129
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:17,033
I had no choice
but to lie, Marj.

130
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,667
When I gave birth to Paolo,

131
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:23,233
I saw how happy Greg was.

132
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,967
How deeply he loved that child.

133
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:32,933
That's why I was afraid
that if I told the truth,

134
00:07:33,067 --> 00:07:34,333
he would kick us out.

135
00:07:34,467 --> 00:07:36,233
We would become homeless.

136
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,733
So, I hid the truth.

137
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:42,400
I didn't want Paolo to grow up
without a name

138
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:45,900
and without a future
because of one mistake.

139
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,833
But that wasn't right.

140
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:53,167
Paolo was saved
but Edward suffered.

141
00:07:55,533 --> 00:07:58,100
Marj, you're a mother too.

142
00:07:59,133 --> 00:08:01,533
You, of all people, should know.

143
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:04,000
I did what I had to do

144
00:08:04,133 --> 00:08:06,167
so Paolo's life
wouldn't be ruined.

145
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:11,167
But, Mom, you stole the right
for Paolo to know the truth.

146
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:16,233
And dad has the right to know
who his real child is.

147
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,000
So he won't push
Edward into prison.

148
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:21,900
Marj, please,
I'm begging you.

149
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:24,833
Don't do anything
that we will all regret.

150
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:27,900
I don't want to completely
destroy our family.

151
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,467
I'm sorry, Mom.

152
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:32,767
But if you can't speak up,

153
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,100
I'll tell Paolo myself.

154
00:08:35,233 --> 00:08:38,933
Because I know he wouldn't want
to continue living a good life

155
00:08:39,067 --> 00:08:42,300
knowing it came
from his sibling's suffering.

156
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:44,133
Marj, please.

157
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:46,533
Please don't tell Paolo
the truth.

158
00:08:46,667 --> 00:08:48,467
Because if you do that,

159
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:51,533
it will be as if you destroyed
our family yourself.

160
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:53,500
Marj, please.

161
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:55,500
But we've been broken
for a long time.

162
00:08:56,767 --> 00:09:01,000
But I need to do this
to protect and save

163
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:03,533
what little remains
of our family.

164
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,433
Mom, Aldrin already knows
the truth.

165
00:09:07,567 --> 00:09:09,833
- What?
- And he can weaponize

166
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,867
this information
to destroy us publicly.

167
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,067
Are you going to wait

168
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:18,533
for dad, Paolo, and Edward
to read it in the papers

169
00:09:18,667 --> 00:09:20,767
and have everyone feast on it?

170
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:25,867
Mom...

171
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:30,833
this is the moment
for you to tell the truth.

172
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:36,233
This is your chance
to correct your mistake.

173
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:39,900
Tell them the truth.

174
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:48,700
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:09:49,067 --> 00:09:51,333
[SOBBING]

176
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:53,300
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

177
00:09:53,433 --> 00:09:58,100
Miss Natividad, the accusation
by Mr. Greg Torrecampo

178
00:09:58,233 --> 00:09:59,800
against his child is serious.

179
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,300
There is evidence.

180
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:05,067
How are you certain that he had
nothing to do with the fire?

181
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:10,633
Because I was there
when it happened.

182
00:10:13,033 --> 00:10:17,633
Because I know
who the real culprit is.

183
00:10:17,767 --> 00:10:19,400
Who, Miss?

184
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:21,333
Was there someone else
who entered the house?

185
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:25,467
No, no, Edward.

186
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,300
There was no one else.

187
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:34,767
I'm the one responsible.

188
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:39,000
I burned your house.

189
00:10:41,267 --> 00:10:43,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

190
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,733
You, Miss?

191
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:48,733
[SOBBING]

192
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:51,167
But you've always been kind
and loyal to us.

193
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:53,233
How could you do that?

194
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:54,833
[SOBBING]

195
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:58,233
I don't even know
how I was able to do it.

196
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:05,333
<i>But like you, I also grew tired
of your family.</i>

197
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:12,967
<i>My anger reached its breaking
point that night.</i>

198
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:17,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:11:20,067 --> 00:11:30,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

200
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:41,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

201
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:59,400
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:07,133
<i> I am not a bad person.</i>

203
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:14,733
<i>But you pushed me to do this,
Greg, Regina.</i>

204
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:20,533
<i>Since you already threw me away
like trash...</i>

205
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:26,267
<i>then let's all lose
our homes together.</i>

206
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:35,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

207
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:45,167
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:12:48,133 --> 00:12:54,967
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

209
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:08,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:19,567
<i>Sorry, Sir Edward, but I don't
want to go to jail.</i>

211
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:26,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:38,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

213
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:48,100
[FIRE CRACKLING]

214
00:13:48,233 --> 00:13:50,833
Edward, forgive me,

215
00:13:50,967 --> 00:13:53,333
I never intended to involve
other people.

216
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:55,067
I only wanted to get back
at your parents

217
00:13:55,233 --> 00:13:57,167
because they were the ones
who wronged me.

218
00:13:58,233 --> 00:14:00,700
- Edward.
- But, Miss, why me?

219
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:04,133
Why did I have to pay
for your sins?

220
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,533
Because I was a coward.

221
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,533
I was afraid that maybe...

222
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:13,533
I might go to jail for life.

223
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:17,867
I thought that if you were
accused,

224
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:21,667
Ma'am Regina and your father
would not file charges.

225
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:26,433
He wouldn't charge you
to avoid public shame.

226
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:31,833
I can no longer bear the guilt
seeing you suffer, Edward.

227
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,200
I am ready.

228
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:36,000
I am ready to pay
for everything,

229
00:14:36,133 --> 00:14:38,133
I am ready to go to jail

230
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:41,567
so I won't add any more
to my sin against you.

231
00:14:43,100 --> 00:14:45,967
Edward, sorry. Sorry, Edward.

232
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,433
I was just really afraid...

233
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:52,400
- I didn't mean to. Sorry.
- [SOBBING]

234
00:14:53,533 --> 00:15:01,633
[SOBBING]

235
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:04,767
Thank you so much, Attorney.

236
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,833
Please just send me the draft
of the complaint tomorrow.

237
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:07,933
Yeah.

238
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:22,967
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

239
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,200
Mom.

240
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:27,000
Why are you crying?

241
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,233
Was Aldrin behind this?

242
00:15:32,167 --> 00:15:33,800
Mom, don't worry, okay?

243
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,167
I already filed a complaint
against him.

244
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:38,333
I'll teach him a lesson
so he'll stop.

245
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:42,467
Paolo, don't go
through with it, okay?

246
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:44,967
Mom, why?

247
00:15:46,667 --> 00:15:49,467
Do you know what he's been
saying about you?

248
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:51,733
My child.

249
00:15:53,767 --> 00:15:55,633
Please don't get angry, okay?

250
00:15:55,767 --> 00:15:57,100
But...

251
00:15:58,533 --> 00:15:59,700
everything...

252
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:08,433
everything Aldrin said is true.

253
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,400
He's not lying.

254
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:22,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:29,533
Are you serious, Mom?

256
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:33,633
I'm really an illegitimate
child?

257
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:39,300
So, all this time,
you were just deceiving me?

258
00:16:42,433 --> 00:16:43,400
My child, my child.

259
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,700
My child, I only did that
because...

260
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:48,700
because I love you.

261
00:16:48,833 --> 00:16:52,000
Because I didn't want
your father to disown you.

262
00:16:52,133 --> 00:16:55,967
I wanted our family
to stay whole, my child.

263
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:57,367
Enough!

264
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:03,200
Don't use love to justify
your lies, Mom!

265
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:09,367
You deceived all of us!

266
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:15,267
If Aldrin hadn't found out
the truth,

267
00:17:15,433 --> 00:17:19,167
if he hadn't exposed you,
would you have confessed?

268
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:22,633
Or would you just keep going
with your lies?

269
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:25,500
Paolo, please, calm down.

270
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:27,700
Don't let your anger
control you.

271
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:31,267
- Please.
- I'm sorry.

272
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:34,433
I'm sorry, I know I should have
told you the truth,

273
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:38,500
but I was afraid
that you'd loathe me.

274
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:39,900
Enough!

275
00:17:40,033 --> 00:17:43,300
I don't want to hear
any more excuses from you.

276
00:17:45,133 --> 00:17:47,667
Every word that comes out
from your mouth

277
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,100
sounds like a poison to me now!

278
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,333
My child...

279
00:17:53,467 --> 00:17:54,900
Please leave now!

280
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,000
Get out!

281
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:02,667
[SOBBING]

282
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,967
Leave! I don't want to see you!

283
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:07,067
I don't even know
who you are anymore!

284
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,500
[EXCLAIMS]

285
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,467
[GLASS SCATTERS]

286
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:23,567
["KATOTOHANAN" BY JESSICA
VILLARUBIN PLAYING]

287
00:18:57,667 --> 00:19:04,800
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:14,900
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:19,800
[CLATTERS]

290
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:22,000
You liar! Liar!

291
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:24,433
Liar! Liar!

292
00:19:24,567 --> 00:19:25,467
Liar!

293
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,367
- Paolo! Paolo!
- Liar! Liar!

294
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,300
Paolo, can you stop that?
Please!

295
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,600
Paolo.

296
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,733
What kind of mother is she?

297
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:40,233
How could she do this to us?

298
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:45,967
All my life, I feel so proud
of being a Torrecampo.

299
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:49,100
I practically worshiped dad.

300
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:54,400
All I ever wanted
was to please him.

301
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:57,733
To make him proud.

302
00:19:57,867 --> 00:20:01,100
Turns out I had no right
to carry his name.

303
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:04,833
Because I was nothing
to the man I idolized.

304
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:09,800
It was all just an act by
my lying and deceitful mother!

305
00:20:11,867 --> 00:20:15,467
Paolo, I know you're angry
and you're hurting.

306
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:18,433
But don't talk about your mother
like that.

307
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:21,967
And you're still defending her?

308
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:25,233
After what she did to us?

309
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:26,500
To me?

310
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,900
Paolo, I'm not defending her.

311
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:33,100
I know your mother and I
don't always agree,

312
00:20:33,233 --> 00:20:38,267
but I can't deny that
she was a good mother to you.

313
00:20:38,433 --> 00:20:41,633
She protected you
in every way she could.

314
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:42,967
Good, Marj?

315
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,400
She deceived me!

316
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:50,000
She let me live in a world
that was never meant for me.

317
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:53,533
Marj, she made a fool out of me!

318
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:58,467
How is that different
from what you did to Ashley?

319
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:03,233
Didn't you also hide
her true identity?

320
00:21:05,767 --> 00:21:09,967
I know you stayed silent,
you lied...

321
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:13,533
because you were thinking
of Ashley's welfare.

322
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:16,333
You didn't want her to be hurt.

323
00:21:16,467 --> 00:21:19,967
You didn't want her to question
herself, her true identity.

324
00:21:21,967 --> 00:21:24,300
Your mother did the same
for you.

325
00:21:24,433 --> 00:21:25,933
Paolo, even if the way
she chose was wrong,

326
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:27,700
it was the only way she knew

327
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:30,100
so you wouldn't lose
everything.

328
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,600
So please, before you judge
your mother,

329
00:21:33,733 --> 00:21:36,333
I hope you think about
what she went through.

330
00:21:38,533 --> 00:21:40,333
Where she was coming from.

331
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:44,867
Because in truth,
both of you were blinded

332
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:47,733
by the desire to protect
your children.

333
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:57,833
[SOBBING]

334
00:21:59,033 --> 00:22:09,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:17,300
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:22:17,433 --> 00:22:20,200
[SOBBING]

337
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:29,833
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

338
00:22:39,867 --> 00:22:40,833
Aldrin.

339
00:22:44,267 --> 00:22:45,767
Yes, Thea?

340
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:47,567
What brings you here?

341
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:51,167
I heard Paolo say
that you told him something

342
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:53,700
that could cause a fight
between him and Edward.

343
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,367
I want to know what that is.

344
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:58,700
Why don't you ask Paolo instead?

345
00:23:00,367 --> 00:23:02,067
Well, whatever it is,

346
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:05,000
it seems he has no intention
of telling us.

347
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:07,500
And it seems he doesn't believe
in what you're saying either.

348
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:09,333
[HUFFS]

349
00:23:11,533 --> 00:23:14,367
That person is truly arrogant,
isn't he?

350
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:17,667
He takes after his father
completely.

351
00:23:18,733 --> 00:23:22,100
I already served him the truth
on a silver platter,

352
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:23,500
yet he's still stubborn.

353
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:24,567
Just be direct with me!

354
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:26,300
What is the truth
you're talking about?

355
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:31,633
Paolo has no right
to act like a golden boy.

356
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,467
Because he's not a real
Torrecampo.

357
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:42,600
He's just an illegitimate child
of his mother.

358
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:50,333
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:23:51,733 --> 00:24:01,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:02,600
Mom?

361
00:24:05,267 --> 00:24:14,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,333
I'm sorry, my child.

363
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:24,800
[SOBBING]

364
00:24:24,933 --> 00:24:30,967
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

365
00:24:32,167 --> 00:24:36,700
[SOBBING]

366
00:24:38,433 --> 00:24:46,000
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:48,000
I'm sorry.

368
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,433
I'm sorry for hurting you.

369
00:24:54,567 --> 00:24:56,433
But, Mom,

370
00:24:56,567 --> 00:25:00,033
I shouldn't be the only one
you should apologize to.

371
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:01,467
Paolo is right, Mom.

372
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:07,033
Edward and dad
need to know the truth.

373
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:20,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:29,233
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:40,467
You're free now.

376
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,767
Thank you.

377
00:25:46,533 --> 00:25:47,733
Edward!

378
00:25:50,267 --> 00:25:52,033
What is that man doing here?

379
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:54,500
Relax, he's on our side.

380
00:25:55,267 --> 00:25:56,533
Thea, have you forgotten?

381
00:25:56,667 --> 00:25:58,700
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- When Ashley was in danger,

382
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:00,267
that man ignored us.

383
00:26:02,133 --> 00:26:05,500
I'm sorry, Edward,
that I couldn't help you before.

384
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:08,433
That's why I'm here now
to make up for it.

385
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,333
We don't need you.

386
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:12,433
Leave now.

387
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:15,233
Edward, please.

388
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:17,800
Please listen first
to what he has to say.

389
00:26:20,467 --> 00:26:21,900
What is she talking about?

390
00:26:22,033 --> 00:26:29,200
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

391
00:26:29,733 --> 00:26:30,600
I have already reserved
a private area

392
00:26:30,733 --> 00:26:32,233
at my friend's restaurant.

393
00:26:32,367 --> 00:26:34,033
We'll take them there
so we can talk.

394
00:26:34,167 --> 00:26:35,167
All right.

395
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:40,300
Edward, we're happy
that you've been cleared.

396
00:26:40,433 --> 00:26:42,067
Come on, come with us.

397
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,133
Stay away from that man.

398
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:44,367
He can't be trusted.

399
00:26:44,500 --> 00:26:45,367
Come on.

400
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:47,133
Wow!

401
00:26:47,367 --> 00:26:50,133
Coming from you, Paolo.

402
00:26:50,267 --> 00:26:52,167
Isn't that rich?

403
00:26:52,300 --> 00:26:53,433
Why?

404
00:26:53,567 --> 00:26:54,600
Are you afraid

405
00:26:54,733 --> 00:26:56,867
that I might tell Edward
something you wouldn't like?

406
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,900
Shut your mouth!

407
00:26:59,033 --> 00:27:00,867
Stop stirring trouble
in our family.

408
00:27:01,933 --> 00:27:05,033
Well, if you've all come here
to do some damage control,

409
00:27:05,167 --> 00:27:06,867
I'm afraid you're all too late.

410
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,500
What do you mean?

411
00:27:10,133 --> 00:27:11,900
We already know everything

412
00:27:12,033 --> 00:27:15,033
that my spouse
is the real Torrecampo

413
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,667
and your spouse
is the real bastard.

414
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:25,233
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

415
00:27:28,100 --> 00:27:31,167
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

416
00:27:31,300 --> 00:27:32,933
<i> All lies...</i>

417
00:27:33,067 --> 00:27:34,200
<i> have an end.</i>

418
00:27:34,333 --> 00:27:35,633
Is it true?

419
00:27:35,767 --> 00:27:37,933
Paolo is an illegitimate child.

420
00:27:38,067 --> 00:27:42,800
In short, he has no right
to dad's wealth and position.

421
00:27:42,933 --> 00:27:44,533
But Paolo is still my brother.

422
00:27:44,667 --> 00:27:46,700
So, if Edward doesn't act,

423
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:48,600
why don't you
take action yourself?

424
00:27:50,533 --> 00:27:52,233
He has an awarding event
that he's attending.

425
00:27:52,367 --> 00:27:55,167
I'm sure he won't be able
to escape you,

426
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:56,867
in front of many people.

427
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,533
Wow!

428
00:27:58,667 --> 00:28:01,400
That's touching!

429
00:28:01,533 --> 00:28:03,600
Well, this is more exciting.

430
00:28:03,733 --> 00:28:07,733
- It can no longer be stopped.
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
